THE STORY WAS ABOUT A BOY WHOSE FATHER GOT A JOB AS A JANITOR IN A LIBRARY.

THE FAMILY WAS POOR AND THE LITTLE BOY STAYED IN THE LIBRARY ALL OF THE TIME, READING BOOKS AND STUDYING. THE LITTLE BOY LOVED THE LIBRARY AND WAS HAPPY THAT HIS FATHER GOT A JOB THERE SO THAT HE COULD HANG OUT AND LEARN.
WHEN THE LITTLE BOY GREW UP, HE BECAME A PROFESSOR BECAUSE HE HAD SPENT SO MUCH TIME IN THE LIBRARY AND WAS VERY SMART.
HE THANKS HIS DAD FOR WORKING THERE BECAUSE HIS LIFE MAY NOT HAVE TURNED OUT SO WELL IF HE DIDN'T WORK THERE.
IN THE STORY A LITTLE BOY FROM A POOR FAMILY LOVED TO HANG OUT IN THE LIBRARY WHERE HIS DAD WAS A JANITOR.
HIS DAD TOOK GREAT PRIDE IN HIS WORK AND EVEN WAXED THE TOP OF THE BOOKSHELVES.
THE LITTLE BOY WOULD HANG OUT IN THE LIBRARY FOR HOURS AND HOURS AND HE LOVED TO READ THE BOOKS. WHEN HE GREW UP, HE BECAME A PROFESSOR BECAUSE HE WAS SO SMART FROM READING BOOKS ALL OF HIS LIFE.
HE THOUGHT THAT IF HIS DAD HADN'T TAKEN THAT JOB HE WOULDN'T KNOW WHERE HE WOULD BE TODAY, BUT BECAUSE HE DID, HIS LIFE TURNED OUT REALLY WELL.
